---
// Calibration — the four numbers that earn the "usebrick" name.
// Count-up animation on reveal (counter.ts). Each brick shows a
// `data-target` (the real value) and a verdict (the natural-language
// restatement the user can read into).
//
// v0.21.0: aiSlopScore is raw amount of slop (lower = cleaner), not
// the inverted cleanliness reading. The 4 numbers below are the
// slopbrick repo's own most-recent self-scan — a real example, not
// a cherry-picked marketing number.

// From `slopbrick scan --workspace packages/slopbrick --brief` on 2026-07-06.
// Shape: aiSlopScore=25, engineeringHygiene=100, security=100, repositoryHealth=57.
// The slopbrick repo's meanSlop is 15 (strict self-scan threshold).

import StructureDemo from './StructureDemo.astro';
---

<section class="section calibration" id="calibration">
  <header class="calibration__head">
    <span class="calibration__label">calibrated, not guessed</span>
    <h2 class="calibration__title">
      The numbers that earn the name <span class="calibration__accent">usebrick</span>.
    </h2>
    <p class="calibration__subhead">
      From <code>slopbrick scan</code> on this site&apos;s own repo. Per-rule
      calibration lives in <code>src/rules/signal-strength.json</code>;
      no score is hand-picked, all are derived from v10-corpus
      precision/recall against 576,750 files.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="calibration__stats">
    <div class="calibration__stat">
      <div class="calibration__value" data-target="25" data-prefix="" data-suffix="">0</div>
      <div class="calibration__axis">AI Slop Score</div>
      <div class="calibration__verdict">low amount of AI slop</div>
    </div>
    <div class="calibration__stat">
      <div class="calibration__value" data-target="100" data-prefix="" data-suffix="">0</div>
      <div class="calibration__axis">Engineering Hygiene</div>
      <div class="calibration__verdict">consistent across 6 categories</div>
    </div>
    <div class="calibration__stat">
      <div class="calibration__value" data-target="100" data-prefix="" data-suffix="">0</div>
      <div class="calibration__axis">Security</div>
      <div class="calibration__verdict">no AI-flagged security risks</div>
    </div>
    <div class="calibration__stat calibration__stat--wide">
      <div class="calibration__value" data-target="57" data-prefix="" data-suffix="">0</div>
      <div class="calibration__axis">Repository Health</div>
      <div class="calibration__verdict">composite, hierarchy + security-weighted</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <StructureDemo />

  <blockquote class="calibration__quote">
    Every rule ships with a recall/FP ratio. A rule that fires more
    noise than signal goes back to <em>defaultOff</em> until it earns
    its way on. <strong>aiSlopScore</strong> uses the natural-reading
    direction (0 = clean, 100 = saturated) — the other three scores
    are &quot;higher = better&quot;. v0.21.0.
    <cite class="calibration__cite">the usebrick calibration contract</cite>
  </blockquote>
</section>
